5","1040–Male":"1040–Overleden","1044–1080":"1044–1080","1045–1098":"1045–1098","1080":"1080","after 1040":"na 1040","1044":"1044","1098":"1098","1075":"1075","1040":"1040","1070":"1070","1019":"1019","1027":"1027","1047":"1047","Abt 1045":"circa 1045","1045":"1045","about 1034":"circa 1034","Normandie, France":"Normandie, Frankrijk","Barnstable, Devon, England":"Devon, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","St Lo, Normandy, France":"Saint-Lô, Normandie, Frankrijk","Normandy, France":"Normandie, Frankrijk","France":"Frankrijk","Manche, Normandy, France":"Manche, Normandie, Frankrijk"},"en":{"1027–1070":"1027–1070","1019–1047":"1019–1047","1019–1075":"1019–1075","1040–1075":"1040–1075","1040–Male":"1040–Deceased","1044–1080":"1044–1080","1045–1098":"1045–1098","1080":"1080","after 1040":"after 1040","1044":"1044","1098":"1098","1075":"1075","1040":"1040","1070":"1070","1019":"1019","1027":"1027","1047":"1047","Abt 1045":"about 1045","1045":"1045","about 1034":"about 1034","Normandie, France":"Normandy, France","Barnstable, Devon, England":"Devon, England, United Kingdom","St Lo, Normandy, France":"Saint-Lô, Normandy, France","Normandy, France":"Normandy, France","France":"France","Manche, Normandy, France":"Manche, Normandy, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Of","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese: Cheng, Jing, Kam Fung, Wai Shing, Wing, Yali, Yuk.","Chinese:","variant Romanization of the surnames 歐 and 區, see   Ou   1 and 2."],"variants":[{"name":"Ou","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Wei, Ying, Ching, Heng, Hong, Jia, Kuang Yu, Li-Ching, Cho, Chong, Chung, Sa.  Southeast Asian Lichun, Ming, Quan, Roeun, Sokhom, Chau, Hai, Leang, Ly, Nhanh, Phan, Pho, Tha.","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 歐, meaning ‘to sing someone's praise’ in ancient Chinese: (i) from the placename Dong Ou (東甌), a fief (in present-day Wenzhou in Zhejiang province) which was granted to Yao in 192  BC . It is said that Yao was a descendant of Wujiang (reigned 355–333  BC ), king of the state of Yue (located mainly in present-day Zhejiang and Jiangxi provinces) during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ). (ii) from the placename Ou Yu (歐餘), the name of a fief (located in present-day Zhejiang province) that was granted to Ti, the second son of Wujiang (reigned 355–333  BC ), king of the state of Yue (located mainly in present-day Zhejiang and Jiangxi provinces) during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ).","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 區, originally denoting an ancient vessel for measurement in ancient Chinese: from the personal name of <i>Ou Zhizi</i> (歐治子), an expert sword-maker who lived during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ). Some of his descendants inherited <i>Ou</i> (歐) as their surname, simplifying the Chinese character 歐 to 區."]}]},{"name":"Normandie","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Armand, Alain, Serge, Adrien, Andre, Aurore, Celine, Clovis, Emile, Gaetan, Gilles, Laurier.","French: from a diminutive of   Normand  . Compare   Normandy  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Normand","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Gaston, Andre, Laurent, Marcel, Pierre, Amie, Donat, Emile, Herve, Jacques, Jean Noel, Jean-Michel.","French and Breton (mainly Finistère; also <b>Le Normand</b>): habitational name for someone from Normandy, a region in northern France (see   Norman  ). Compare   Lenormand  .","Scottish (Fife): variant of   Norman  ."]},{"name":"Normandy","meanings":["English: habitational name from Normandy in northern France. This surname is now rare in Britain.","Americanized form of French   Normandin  ."]}]},{"name":"Helena","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   Helen  , used also 